data.enText: a tool with a wooden handle and a heavy metal blade, used for chopping wood, cutting down trees, etc.
if sb gets the axe , they lose their job; if an institution or a project gets the axe , it is closed or stopped, usually because of a lack of money

data.chText: 艰苦挣扎的默西赛德公司有多达300名工人面临被解雇。
data.enText: Up to 300 workers are facing the axe at a struggling Merseyside firm.

data.chText: 病人高兴的是当地医院得以免遭关闭。
data.enText: Patients are delighted their local hospital has been saved from the axe.
to have private reasons for being involved in sth or for arguing for a particular cause

data.chText: 她毫无私心，这样做只是出于对他们安全的担心。
data.enText: She had no axe to grind and was only acting out of concern for their safety.

data.chText: 精简（机构等）；大量削减（经费等）
data.enText: to get rid of a service, system, etc. or to reduce the money spent on it by a large amount

data.chText: 其他盈利较少的服务项目预定今年稍晚将大量削减。
data.enText: Other less profitable services are to be axed later this year.
to remove sb from their job
Jones has been axed from the team.
to kill sb with an axe

ex.chText: 那名教师被秘密开除了。
员工上班时间玩电脑游戏会遭到解雇。
ex.enText: Employees can be dismissed/fired/sacked for playing computer games at work.

synonyms.bx: 指正式解除某人的职务，常可与 fire，sack 换用。

ex.chText: 该公司周四宣布计划裁员180人。
ex.enText: The company announced Thursday their plan to axe 180 employees.
Vera has been axed from the team.

synonyms.bx: 指突然解除某人的职务。

ex.chText: 他刚刚因为迟到被解雇。
ex.enText: He has just been fired/sacked for being late.

ex.chText: 公司把他开除了，他不知该怎么办。
ex.enText: The company fired/sacked him and he didn't know what to do.

synonyms.bx: 指强行解除某人的职务，常可与 sack 换用。

ex.chText: 这家连锁店10月份裁员500人。
ex.enText: The chain store laid off 500 workers in October.

ex.chText: 经济危机期间，数百万工人被解雇。
ex.enText: Millions of workers were laid off during the economic crisis.

synonyms.bx: 指因为没有工作可做而解雇员工。

ex.chText: 委员会罢免了那名腐败的官员。
ex.enText: The committee removed the corrupt official.
Congress has the right to remove the President from office.

synonyms.bx: 指免除某人的职务，尤指罢免身居要职者。

ex.chText: 他没做错事却被解雇了。
ex.enText: He was sacked from the job, although he did nothing wrong.

ex.chText: 爸爸因为喝醉酒而遭到解雇。
ex.enText: Dad was sacked for being drunk.

data.chText: 她毫无私心，这样做只是出于对他们安全的担心。
data.enText: She had no axe to grind and was only acting out of concern for their safety.

tr: an edge tool with a heavy bladed head mounted across a handle

example: The NSF axed the research program and stopped funding it

tr: chop or split with an ax

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 ax

value.def: An axe is a tool used for cutting wood. It consists of a heavy metal blade which is sharp at one edge and attached by its other edge to the end of a long handle.
If someone's job or something such as a public service or a television programme is axed, it is ended suddenly and without discussion.

example.ex: Community projects are being axed by hard-pressed social services departments.
example.tran: 处于困境的社会服务部门被迫砍掉社区项目。

value.def: If a person or institution is facing the axe, that person is likely to lose their job or that institution is likely to be closed, usually in order to save money.

example.ex: St Bartholomew's is one of four London hospitals facing the axe.
example.tran: 圣巴塞洛缪医院是伦敦4个面临关闭的医院之一。

value.tran: （通常为节省资金而进行的）解雇，撤销，关闭

value.def: If someone has an axe to grind, they are doing something for selfish reasons.

example.ex: He seems like a decent bloke and I've got no axe to grind with him.
example.tran: 他看上去像是个正派的家伙，而且我对他没有任何企图。

value.tran: 有私心；有个人打算；另有企图
